        <h2>Norwegian Forest Cat Breed</h2>
        <br />
        <table border="1" class="tab">
            <tr>
                <th>Characteristic</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Size</td>
                <td>Larger than average cat</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Coat</td>
                <td>
                    Semi-longhair, longer in winter and shorter in summer; smooth, glossy outer coat with a woolly undercoat
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Body</td>
                <td>Long, muscular, strongly built; long legs and bushy tail</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Head</td>
                <td>Long, triangular; straight profile; high-set ears with tufted tips</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Coat Markings</td>
                <td>
                    Any color except chocolate, lilac, or Siamese pattern; may have white markings on paws, chest, belly, or
                    face
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Coat Texture</td>
                <td>
                    Water-repellent; full coat includes ruff, shirtfront, knickerbockers, and tufts of hair between toes
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
